obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (48851)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48851&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Disturbed Areas (Special`
  line `Courts) Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different States or for different parts`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2.15th August, 1976, vide notification No. S.O. 549(E), dated 13thAugust, 1976, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (48852)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48852&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(b) "disturbed area" means an area declared as a disturbed area under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) period of disturbance, in relation to a disturbed area, means the period during which it is to be`
  line `a disturbed area for the purposes of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "scheduled offence" means an offence specified in the Schedule being an offence forming part`
  line `or arising out of, or connected with, any such disturbance as is referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) "Special Court" means a Special Court constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act, and defined in the Code shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (48853)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Declaration of an area as disturbed area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48853&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a State Government is satisfied that`
  line
  line `(i) there was, or`
  line
  line `(ii) there is,`
  line
  line `in any area within a State extensive disturbance of the public peace and tranquillity, by reason of`
  line `differences or disputes between members of different religious, racial, language or regional groups or`
  line `castes or communities, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such area to be a disturbed`
  line area.
  line
  line `(2) A notification issued under sub-section (1) in respect of any area shall specify the period during`
  line `which the area shall, for the purposes of this section, be a disturbed area and where the State Government`
  line `is satisfied that there was such disturbance of public peace and tranquillity as is referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) in that area from any date prior to the issue of such notification, the period specified in the notification`
  line `may commence from that date:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) no period commencing from a date earlier than three months before the date of publication of`
  line `the notification shall be specified therein; and`
  line
  line `(b) so much of the period specified in such notification as is subsequent to the date of publication`
  line `of the notification shall not, in the first instance, exceed three months but the State Government may`
  line `amend such notification to extend such period from time to time by any period not exceeding three months at any one time if in the opinion of the State Government there continues to be in such area`
  line `such disturbance of public peace and tranquillity as is referred to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the State Government is satisfied that there is no longer such disturbance`
  line `of public peace and tranquillity as is referred to in sub-section (1) in such area, it shall amend the`
  line `notification issued under that sub-section in respect of that area to limit the period specified therein`
  line `(whether originally or by amendment under the preceding proviso) accordingly.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.--In section 3 of the Disturbed Areas (Special Courts) Act, 1976 (Central`
  line `Act 77 of 1976) in sub-section (1), after the words "castes or communities", the words "or due to any`
  line `other reason" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 49 of 1981, s. 2]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Manipur
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.--In section 3 of the Disturbed Areas (Special Courts) Act, 1976,`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the Principal Act):--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), between the words, "communities", and "it may", the following words,`
  line `brackets and figures shall be inserted, namely--`
  line
  line `"or by reason of extension and indiscriminate armed violence by members of an association`
  line `declared as unlawful association under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(i) In clause (a) of the proviso, the word "and" appearing at the end shall be deleted, and the`
  line `words, letters and brackets, "save in respect of the cases referred to in clause (aa)", shall be`
  line `inserted in the beginning, and`
  line
  line `(ii) below clause (a) of the proviso so amended, the following clause shall be added,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"(aa) in respect of extensive and indiscriminate armed violence by members of any`
  line `association declared as unlawful association under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention)`
  line `Act, 1967, no period commencing from a date earlier than the date of publication of the`
  line `notification, if any, under section 3 of the Armed Forces (Special Powers) Act, 1958 (28 of`
  line `1958) in respect of that area or earlier than two years before the date of publication of the`
  line `notification under sub-section (1), shall be specified therein; and".`
  line
  line `[Vide Manipur Act 11 of 1982, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (48854)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48854&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, for the purpose of providing`
  line `speedy trial of scheduled offences committed in disturbed areas, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute as many Special Courts as may be necessary in or in relation to such disturbed area or areas as`
  line `may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a single judge who shall be appointed by the High Court upon a`
  line `request made by the State Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, the word "appoint" shall have the meaning given to it in the`
  line `Explanation to section 9 of the Code.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a judge of a Special Court unless—`
  line
  line `(a) he is qualified for appointment as a judge of a High Court, or`
  line
  line `(b) he has, for a period of not less than one year, been a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions`
  line Judge.
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), a person shall not be eligible for being`
  line `appointed as, and for being, a Judge of a Special Court in any State after he has attained the age at which`
  line `Sessions Judges in that State have to retire from service.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (48855)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Jurisdiction of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48855&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code or any other`
  line `law, a scheduled offence committed in any disturbed area at any time during the period during which it is`
  line `a disturbed area shall be triable, whether during or after such period, only by the Special Court constituted`
  line `in or in relation to the disturbed area in which the offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) When trying any scheduled offence, a Special Court may also try any offence other than the`
  line `scheduled offence with which the accused may, under the Code, be charged at the same trial if the offence`
  line `is connected with the scheduled offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (48856)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48856&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every scheduled offence shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court may take cognizance of any scheduled offence,—`
  line
  line `(a) where under the Code such offence is an offence triable exclusively by a Court of Session,`
  line `upon its being committed to it under section 209 of the Code as if the Special Court were a Court of`
  line Session;
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, upon a police report of the facts together with a certificate from the public`
  line `prosecutor to the effect that the offence is triable exclusively by the Special Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a scheduled offence is an offence triable exclusively by a Court of Session under the Code,`
  line `a Special Court shall have all the powers of a Court of Session and shall try such offence as if it were a`
  line `Court of Session, so far as may be in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code for trial before`
  line `a Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a scheduled offence is an offence which is punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding three years but which, according to the provisions of the Code, is not an offence triable`
  line `exclusively by a Court of Session, a Special Court may on taking cognizance of the offences perform the`
  line `functions of a Magistrate under section 207 of the Code and thereafter try such offence so far as may be in`
  line `accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code for trial before a Court of Session as if the Special`
  line `Court were a Court of Session and the case had been committed to it for trial under the provisions of the`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(5) Where a scheduled offence is punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years`
  line `or with fine or with both, a Special Court may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 260 or section 262 of the Code, try the offence in a summary way in accordance with the`
  line `procedure prescribed in the Code and the provisions of sections 263 to 265 of the Code, shall so far as`
  line `may be, apply to such trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that when, in the course of a summary trial under this sub-section, it appears to the Special`
  line `Court that the nature of the case is such that it is undesirable to try it summarily, the Special Court shall`
  line `recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the manner`
  line `provided by the provisions of the Code for the trial of such offence and the said provisions shall apply to`
  line `and in relation to a Special Court as they apply to and in relation to a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be`
  line `lawful for a Special Court to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding two years.`
  line
  line `(6) A Special Court may, with a view to obtaining the evidence of any person suspected to have been`
  line `directly or indirectly concerned in, or privy to, an offence, tender a pardon to such person on condition of`
  line `his making a full and true disclosure of the whole circumstances within his knowledge relating to the`
  line `offence and to every other person concerned whether as principal or abettor in the commission thereof`
  line `and any pardon so tendered shall, for the purposes of section 308 of the Code, be deemed to have been`
  line `tendered under section 307 thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (48857)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to transfer cases to regular courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48857&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where, after taking cognizance of any offence, a`
  line `Special Court is of opinion that the offence is not a scheduled offence, it shall, notwithstanding that it has`
  line `no Jurisdiction to try the case, transfer the case for trial to any court having jurisdiction under the Code`
  line `and the court to which the case is transferred may proceed with the case as if it had taken cognizance of`
  line `the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (48858)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48858&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may exercise, so far as they may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code on a High Court, as if a Special Court is a`
  line `Court of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (48859)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Overriding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48859&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall have notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code or any other law, but save as expressly provided in this Act, the provisions of the`
  line `Code shall, in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply to the proceedings`
  line `before a Special Court; and for the purposes of the said provisions of the Code, the Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Court of Session and the person conducting a prosecution before a Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1),`
  line `the provisions of sections 326 and 475 of the Code shall, so far as may be, apply to the proceedings before`
  line `a Special Court, and for this purpose references in those provisions to a Magistrate shall be construed as`
  line `references to the Special Court.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Manipur
  line
  line `Amendment of section 9.--In section 9 of the Principal Act, after sub-section (2), the following`
  line `explanation shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Explanation : --The evidence recorded in the trial of a scheduled offence by a Court of Sessions or`
  line `Magistrate before it or he has ceased to exercise jurisdiction therein shall, for the purpose of section`
  line `326 of the Code, be construed as evidence so recorded by the predecessor of the Special Court".`
  line
  line `[Vide Manipur Act 11 of 1982, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (48860)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077&sectionId=48860&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00006_197677_1517807319077
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall affect the jurisdiction exercisable by, or the procedure`
  line `applicable to, any court or other authority under any law relating to the naval, military or air forces or any`
  line `other armed forces of the Union.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of any such law as is referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1), a Special Court shall be deemed to be a court of ordinary criminal justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
